column5: apparently this Moose was shot in Russia and weighed in at 2500lbs and measured 15 feet at the head?  that's 1000 lbs bigger than a big Canadian Bull Moose..
They used angles to make the moose look bigger, but he's still a monster. Not quite as big as PF the FF, but big all the same.
Maybe it lived near Chernobyl?  Burt
He looks like the first hunter to win a trip back to the Pleistocene era.....up next cave bear!
Pretty hard to tell without seeing the rest of the body.  That's a pretty impressive rack none the less.  Cheers  Craig
